==English==
===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1910|1910]], from [[Modern Latin]], from {{G.}} [[Schizophrenie]], coined by [[w:Eugen Bleuler|Eugen Bleuler]], from {{Gr.}} [[schizo-]], from [[skhizein]], "to [[split]]" + [[phren-]], "[[mind]]", from [[phrenos]], hence, "split mind." 

===Pronunciation===
*[[AHD]]: [skĭt′səfrēnēə] or [skĭt′səfrĕnēə]

===Noun===
'''schizophrenia'''
#A [[psychiatric]] [[diagnosis]] denoting a [[persistent]], often [[chronic]], mental illness variously affecting [[behavior]], [[thinking]], and [[emotion]].

